way the text and equations were set on the page. In this new edition of this classic work, mathematical physicist Nicholas Wheeler has completely reset the book in TeX, making the text and equations far easier to read. He has also corrected a handful of typographic errors, revised some sentences for clarity and readability, provided an index for the first time, and added prefatory remarks drawn from the writings of Léon Van Hove and Freeman Dyson. The result brings new life to an essential work in theoretical physics and mathematics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aMatrix mechanics. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Quantum Theory.2bisacsh  aErwin Schrödinger.  aHilbert space.  aMax Born.  aPascual Jordan.  aPaul Dirac.  aWerner Heisenberg.  aabstract Hilbert space.  acausal and statistical methods.  acausal change.  acausal relations.  aclosed linear manifolds.  acommutative operators.  acomposite systems.  adeductive development.  aeigenvalue problem.  aenergy.  ageometry.  amacroscopic measurement.  amathematical basis.  amathematical equations.  amathematical tools.  amathematician.  amathematics.  ameasurement.  ameasuring process.  anature.  aquantum mechanical ensembles.  aquantum mechanical literature.  aquantum mechanics.  aquantum statistics.  aquantum theory.  aradiation theory.  areversibility.  asimultaneous measurability.  astates.  astatistical ensemble.  astatistical formulas.  astatistical relations.  astatistical theory.  astatistics.  atheoretical physics.  athermodynamic observations.  athermodynamics.  atransformation theory.  auncertainty relations.  awave mechanical method.  awave mechanics.1 aBeyer, Robert T.1 aBeyer, Robert T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWheeler, Nich